            'Owning concept to production at Amazon GRAS means: identifying the need (vendor system gap or new capability), defining requirements with stakeholders, evaluating vendor options, designing custom hardware where needed, prototyping, testing in realistic conditions, iterating based on field feedback, getting approval for deployment, writing procedures for multi-site rollout, and supporting the system in production. Your RA-AST is the full lifecycle \u2014 from blank page through quality approval to Chihuahua deployment.',
